TY  - JOUR
T1  - Consistent estimation of limited dependent variable models despite misspecification of distribution
AU  - Ruud, Paul A.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
SP  - 157
EP  - 187
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/06/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(86)90017-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407686900175
AB  - By exploiting conditions on the behavior of regressors, estimators are developed which are consistent, up to a factor of proportionality, for the slope coefficients of the regression function of a imperfectly observed dependent variable. Limited dependent variables are a special case of interest. The consistency is robust to misspecification of the distribution of the latent dependent variable. The estimators are weighted pseudo maximum likelihood estimators which can be readily computed using popular methods and software.
